Feature/prevent exec on synthetic constructors

Prevent execution on synthetic constructors of annotated classes.

Synthetic constructors should not be logged.
i.e. When inner class has a private constructor, the synthetic constructor generated by compiler should not be logged by Hugo.

i.e. Make @DebugLog annotated inner class' constructor private.

Prevent execution of synthetics

Prevent execution on synthetic methods of annotated classes.

Synthetic methods should not be logged.
i.e. When inner class has a private method, the synthetic method generated by compiler should not be logged by Hugo.

Update example to have synthetics when compiled

i.e. @DebugLog annotated inner class has a private method

Merge pull request #36 from joninvski/use_top_gradlew

Use gradlew for hugo-example (not gradle of OS)

Use gradlew for hugo-example (not gradle of OS)

There is a bug when the following tasks are executed:

cleanExample
assembleExample
installExample
In these tasks the gradle of the system is used instead of gradlew.
This leads to strange errors when the two versions are different.

The simple correction consisted on changing the command to execute
from 'gradle to '../gradlew'.

task cleanExample(type: Exec) {
    executable = '../gradlew'
    workingDir = project.file('hugo-example')
    ...
